    "summary": "Anna Theeuwes has over 25 years of experience in advising on international tax matters, first with PriceWaterhouseCoopers in Brussels, Belgium and subsequently within the Royal Dutch Shell group out of The Hague, Netherlands.\n\nShe is a frequent contributor to UN and OECD tax debates on international tax and climate change related tax matters and is recognized as one of the leading tax contributors on the subject. She is currently chairing the BusinessEurope Green Tax Group, the Dutch employers' organisations Environmental and Energy Tax Working group and represents Tax Executives Institute at the EU Platform for Tax Good Governance. \nShe has been chairing the European Direct Tax Committee with Tax Executives Institute (TEI), and has been a member of Dutch, Europe and internationally focused tax committees.\n\nShe is a Board member for a number of companies and public institutions.",
